#   ULOG-001: wtlog/refs files get truncated to 0 bytes ‚Äî enumerate & repro the scenarios

`wtlog` (ULOG append-log) and `refs` tip files in beagle stores were found **truncated to 0 bytes while their companion `.keeper` object packs survived intact** ‚Äî live commit history became unreachable (`NOTAWT` in a worktree, `WIREFAIL`/`WIRECLFL` on clone, `GRAFFAIL` on resolve) even though **no objects were lost**. This is the same class as the once-fixed 9p `O_TRUNC` fallback wipe, but it recurred in an **ext4** store under an as-yet-unproven trigger. Goal: enumerate every code path that can leave a zero-length ULOG/refs, **repro each (repro-first, [CLAUDE] ¬ß17)**, and make ULOG-open / refs-write crash-safe (write-temp-then-rename + fsync, never in-place `O_TRUNC` the live log; treat a 0-byte log as "rebuild", not "empty"). See [Issues], [CLAUDE], [[DIS-033]].

##  Issues
The wipe is ULOG/refs-specific, not a whole-store loss, and the exact trigger is unproven.

 -  Forensics (`~/.be`, ext4 root fs): `~/.be/beagle/refs` 0 B (mtime 21:05), top `~/.be/wtlog` 0 B (21:45), and `~/.be/{dogs,abc,localhost}/wtlog` all 0 B ‚Äî **yet** object packs survived (`localhost/0000000001.keeper` 32 MB, `abc/‚Ä¶keeper` 799 KB) and sibling refs survived (`localhost/refs` 45 B, `abc/refs` 145 B, `dogs/refs` 554 B). So only specific `wtlog`/`refs` files zeroed, never the objects.
 -  Symptom chain: zeroed store `refs` ‚Üí `be get file://‚Ä¶?/beagle` clone fails `WIREFAIL`/`WIRECLFL` (nothing to serve) and **spawns a stray nested `~/.be/.be/` shard**; a worktree whose `.be` wtlog is zeroed reports `NOTAWT` (this is how the URI-002 worktree got busted).
 -  Context of the incident: prior session ran heavy parallel builds across 22 worktrees with root fs at ~94 % (ENOSPC pressure), many concurrent `be` processes sharing one `~/.be`; the 21:00‚Äì21:05 window coincides with a `be get be://localhost` clone creating `~/.be/localhost/` + `~/.be/beagle/` (whose refs was 0 from creation).
 -  Self-inflicted data point (this session, 06:49): re-running `be get file://‚Ä¶?/beagle` against the already-damaged store created **more** stray 0-byte files (`~/.be/.be/{wtlog,beagle/refs}`, `~/.be/refs`) via the elided-store/secondary-wt path ‚Äî i.e. the clone path writes empty logs when the source refs are empty (supports H4).

##  Blockers
The 21:05 trigger can't be pinned from forensics alone ‚Äî no transcript of the prior session. Must reproduce each hypothesis.

##  Planned
Repro every zeroing scenario, then make ULOG/refs writes atomic.

 -  **H1 ‚Äî ENOSPC** (unproven): an in-place `O_TRUNC` open of wtlog/refs then a write that fails on a full fs leaves 0 bytes. Caveat: the fs was ~94 % (‚âà1.5 G free) ‚Äî *near*-full, not provably `ENOSPC` at 21:05, so this is weaker than first claimed; H3/H4 align better with the 21:00‚Äì21:05 clone activity. Repro: a small quota'd/tmpfs store filled to genuine 0-free, then `be post`/`be get`, inspect wtlog/refs.
 -  **H2 ‚Äî 9p `MAP_SHARED` fallback (RULED OUT for this incident)**: the damaged store, all worktrees, and `$HOME/.be` are on `/dev/vda3` **ext4** (`df -T` confirmed); the only 9p mount is `~/src` (the wiki) and no store lives there. So the once-fixed 9p `O_TRUNC`-fallback is **not** the trigger here. Keep only as a general durability check: confirm that fix covers every ULOG open site, in case a store is ever placed on a 9p mount.
 -  **H3 ‚Äî concurrent-writer race**: many parallel `be` processes against one shared `~/.be`; the truncate/rewrite window of a wtlog/refs may not be covered by the `.lock`/`.lock.spot` files. Repro: N concurrent `be post`/`be get` to the same store, check for a zeroed log.
 -  **H4 ‚Äî clone / secondary-wt path**: `be get be://localhost?/beagle` then a `file:` secondary writes an empty `refs` when the source is empty/elided (reproduced at 06:49 above; cf. the legacy elided-store crash). Repro: chain clone ‚Üí secondary against an empty-refs project.
 -  **H5 ‚Äî process killed mid-write**: `SIGKILL`/OOM after `O_TRUNC`, before the write completes. Repro: kill `be` between open and write under `strace`.
 -  **Fix direction**: ULOG/refs writes go to a temp file + `fsync` + atomic `rename`; never `O_TRUNC` the live log in place; on open, a 0-byte wtlog/refs is rebuilt from the surviving objects/sibling refs rather than trusted as empty. Add a regression that asserts a write interrupted by ENOSPC/SIGKILL leaves the prior log intact.

